===Noun===
[[Image:Kakashi2.jpg|thumb||scarecrows in a rice paddy in Japan]]
{{en-noun}}

# {{l|en|An [[effigy]], typically made of [[straw]] and dressed in old clothes, fixed to a [[pole]] in a field to [[deter]] [[bird]]s from [[eating]] [[seed]]s or [[crop]]s planted there.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively|pejorative}} {{l|en|A [[tall]], [[thin]], [[awkward]] person.}}
#* {{quote-book
|year=1749
|author=Henry Fielding
|authorlink=Henry Fielding
|title=The History of Tom Jones, a Foundling
|passage=A consultation was now entered into how to proceed in order to discover the mother. A scrutiny was first made into the characters of the female servants of the house, who were all acquitted by Mrs Wilkins, and with apparent merit; for she had collected them herself, and perhaps it would be difficult to find such another set of '''scarecrows'''.
}}
# {{lb|en|figurative}} {{l|en|Anything that appears [[terrifying]] but offers no [[danger]].}}
#: ''A '''scarecrow''' set to frighten fools away.'' &mdash; {{w|John Dryden|Dryden}}
# {{l|en|A person clad in [[rag]]s and [[tatter]]s.}}
#: ''No eye hath seen such '''scarecrows'''. I'll not march with them through Coventry, that's flat.'' &mdash; {{w|William Shakespeare|Shakespeare}}
# {{lb|en|UK|dialect}} {{l|en|A [[bird]], the [[black tern]].}}

